0.title: Rules
0.body:
Rules for new players:

http://www.vassalengine.org/mediawiki/images/e/ed/GI_JOE_TCG_Rulebook.pdf

The game isn't super complicated, but there's too many details to list here. I recommend looking at the above PDF if you're new and want to learn how to play. It also explains how to build your own deck if you wish to do so.


Below are special rules for 3-4 player games ONLY:

3 and 4 players are unofficial, but nonetheless supported here (there's room on the board and pre-determined card slots for 3rd and 4th players). Below are my custom rules for how to play a 3 or 4 player game. The concept for both is the same:

Game is played FFA (Free For All), If there are 3 players, Player 2 (who goes second) gets 16 supply points. If there are 4 players, both Player 2 and 3 get 16 supply points. Player 1 gets 15 Supply Points and the last player gets 17. Turn order is determined clockwise based on who is chosen to go first, and each following game rotates clockwise on who goes first.

During 1 on 1 combat, you can only choose to fight a player who has not been selected to be fought yet. This ensures everybody gets 2 fights (one offense, one defense).

During Firefights, after you shoot your first target with enough points to be lethal (not counting hidden modifiers like Cobra Commander), you must then shoot a target owned by a different player. You must have used lethal damage on a unit from each enemy player before you can shoot a second target owned by a single player.

Cards in the back rank during a Firefight do not move up until all players have finished using their Firefight cards. Leftover hits from one player are discarded after they end their Firefight phase, and can not be used to team up with another player.

All special abilities target only a single player. For example, Firefly's Sabotage ability can only be used on one enemy player (of owner's choice), this also goes for things like Tripwire's Detect, Suppressive Fire, or Counterintelligence.

If a card that modified the power of another card is killed during the Firefight (for example, Lifeline, a driver manning a Vehicle, a soldier with Support, etc.), the next player(s) then use the new power value of your cards when placing hits on them. An example of this scenario would be that Player 1 uses Long Range to destroy the driver behind Player 3's vehicle. Player 2 may then target that vehicle for its Unmanned strength during his or her Firefight phase.

A player using Cobra Commander, Ruthless Despot's Favor ability may reveal the card they have chosen at any time to give their chosen solider +4 power, but if he does not reveal the soldier that has been dealt lethal damage after one player's Firefight cards have been applied, that unit is destroyed. If the card is revealed and the chosen soldier is saved from death, then the next player may target that soldier (who still has the +4 bonus) and kill them with appropriate lethal damage during their Firefight phase (none of the previous hits carry over, full damage must be dealt).

If a player uses Chief Torpedo as a Boost card, only the two players involved in that battle draw an extra boost card, and the extra fight must be fought between those two players only.

If Killer Whale's Emergency Evac is chosen to be triggered during a Firefight Phase, it may immediately move to the front rank and have the rescued soldier be placed behind it. The next player
may then target the Killer Whale (for its full Manned strength) during their Firefight phase. If Emergency Evac is not used, Killer Whale remains safe in the back rank, though any discarded soldiers that aren't from the final Firefight phase can not be rescued.
